Principe
========
Board Arduino Nano + NRF24L01 mySensors radio module -> Jeedom

We are using:

  Teleinfo:
    - one digital input serial data
    - one digital output for LED

IRQ
===

The hardware IRQ0/IRQ1 (D2/D3) are left free.

http://playground.arduino.cc/Main/PinChangeInterrupt
https://code.google.com/archive/p/arduino-pinchangeint/issues/7
---------------------------------------------------------------
Due to the presence of the NRF24 radio module, the PCINT0 vector has only one free pin.
This pin is allocated to Teleinfo input serial (and so to SoftwareSerial library).

We choose to only use the single PCINT1 vector to all other three DRS155 modules.
So that PCINT2 vector (port D) may be left unused.

11/03/2017
==========
It happens that the Arduino Nano is not able to handle both the teleInfo and the DRS155 codes
because the whole program needs 1937 bytes of heap frame on a 2048 total available.
So we build two sensors:
- mysTeleinfo
- mysDrs155.

